# AI Message Responder

AI Message Responder is a **desktop tool** that can automatically reply to messages you receive on apps like WhatsApp, Discord, and more – on any platform where chat is visible on your screen.[page:26]

It uses a smart screen-capture system to read your chat area (you choose and crop the region), sends the text to AI, and then types and sends the reply for you automatically.[page:26]

> Perfect for busy people, streamers, community managers, and anyone who wants smart auto‑replies without needing custom bots.

---

## ✨ Features

- Auto‑reply to messages on **WhatsApp, Discord, and other chat apps** (anything that appears on your screen).[page:26]  
- Custom crop area so the app only “sees” your chat, not your whole screen.[page:26]  
- **Bot personality system** – fully customize how your AI behaves and talks.  
- Uses AI to generate natural responses based on the incoming message.  
- Automatically types the reply into the input box and sends it for you.[page:26]  
- No need for API access to WhatsApp / Discord bots – works purely from your screen.  
- Easy to start/stop whenever you want.

---

## 🧠 Bot Personality

AI Message Responder lets you create your own **bot personality** so every reply feels unique and on‑brand.

You can define rules like:

> “You are Lightning Bot. You only reply about yourself. Speak in the same language as the user. Keep answers short and confident.”

Examples of what you can customize:

- Name and identity (e.g. “Lightning Bot”, “Support Bot”, “Anime Friend”).  
- Tone (funny, serious, professional, chill, etc.).  
- Allowed topics (only talk about yourself, only talk about tech, avoid politics, etc.).  
- Language behavior (always reply in the user’s language, or force a specific language).  

Once you set a personality, all replies follow those rules until you change them.

---

## 🚀 How It Works

1. You open your chat app (WhatsApp, Discord, etc.) and keep the chat window visible.[page:26]  
2. In AI Message Responder, you select and crop the chat area once.[page:26]  
3. The app continuously reads new messages from that region using screen capture + OCR.  
4. The message text is sent to an AI model, which generates a reply.  
5. The app automatically types the reply into the chat input box and sends it.

